{"CALK":[{"def":"To drive tarred oakum into the seams between the planks of (a ship, boat, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"To make an indentation in the edge of a metal plate, as along a seam in a steam boiler or an iron ship, to force the edge of the upper plate hard against the lower and so fill the crevice.","pos":""}],"CALKER":[{"def":"A calk on a shoe.","pos":""}],"CALKIN":[{"def":"A calk on a shoe.","pos":""}],"CALKING":[{"def":"The act or process of making seems tight, as in ships, or of furnishing with calks, as a shoe, or copying, as a drawing.","pos":""}]}